{% set addressCode %}<address>
  John Smith<br />
  123 Main Street<br />
  Springfield, IL 62704
</address>{% endset %}

{% set poetryCode %}<p>
  Roses are red,<br />
  Violets are blue,<br />
  Sugar is sweet,<br />
  And so are you.
</p>{% endset %}

{% set antiPatternCode %}<!-- Wrong: using br for spacing -->
<p>First paragraph</p>
<br /><br />
<p>Second paragraph</p>

<!-- Right: use margin or layout -->
<layout-stack data-layout-gap="l">
  <p>First paragraph</p>
  <p>Second paragraph</p>
</layout-stack>{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;br&gt;</code> element produces a line break in text. It is a void element (no closing tag). Use it only where the line break is an intrinsic part of the content &mdash; addresses, poetry, song lyrics &mdash; not for visual spacing between blocks.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Postal addresses:</strong> Line breaks between street, city, postal code</li>
      <li><strong>Poetry and lyrics:</strong> Line breaks within stanzas</li>
      <li><strong>Structured text:</strong> Where line breaks carry meaning in the content</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>When NOT to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Spacing between paragraphs:</strong> Use <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> elements or <a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/layout-stack/"><code>&lt;layout-stack&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li><strong>Visual gaps:</strong> Use CSS <code>margin</code> or <code>gap</code></li>
      <li><strong>Separating sections:</strong> Use <a href="/docs/elements/native/hr/"><code>&lt;hr&gt;</code></a> for thematic breaks</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/br-examples.html" url="br-examples.html" title="Line break examples" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Address formatting">{{ addressCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Poetry">{{ poetryCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Anti-Pattern: Spacing</h2>
    <p>Never use multiple <code>&lt;br&gt;</code> elements for vertical spacing. Use semantic structure and CSS instead:</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Wrong vs right spacing">{{ antiPatternCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Screen readers typically announce a line break as a pause</li>
      <li>Multiple consecutive <code>&lt;br&gt;</code> elements are confusing for screen reader users &mdash; they may hear multiple pauses with no content</li>
      <li>Use <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> elements for distinct paragraphs so screen readers can navigate by paragraph</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

